l, rise and become forests.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nCreate a world for yourself in which you can rest,until then stay restless.\n\n- Akash Lakhotia, World Hypnotized: Making of the Fuhrer\n|\nThere is no rest for the humble except in despising the great, whose only thought of the people is inspired by self-interest or sadism.\n\n- Louis-Ferdinand Céline, Journey to the End of the Night\n|\nThe future is an infinite succession of presents, and to live now as we think human beings should live, in defiance of all that is bad around us, is itself a marvelous victory.\n\n- Howard Zinn, You Can't Be Neutral on a Moving Train: A Personal History of Our Times\n|\nI was excited to do something, even if I didn't know what it was. I think you need that feeling—that excitement, that fire—to make your dreams a reality. (p.59)\n\n- Injap Sia, Life Principles\n|\nA flower does not bloom for itself, but for the world; do likewise.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nI love the silent hour of night,For blissful dreams may then arise,Revealing to my charmed sightWhat may not bless my waking eyes.\n\n- Anne Brontë, Best Poems of the Brontë Sisters\n|\n...notice all the many beautiful things, nature, your own soul, stuff other people do.... like help out, smile, create, dance...\n\n- Jay\n|\nPeople are like the waves, all similar, none the same\n\n- Benny Bellamacina, THE SCOOTER FIVE | rhyming book 1 | strawberry bees\n|\nMy dreams had to be His dreams, the ones He placed in my heart. They couldn't be the ones I thought I should have, or needed for the purpose of making other people like me.\n\n- Stormie Omartian, Stormie: A Story of Forgiveness and Healing\n|\nre: cutting glass...'You have to be in command of the glass, telling it where to release its hold on itself. Just like life. Otherwise it will splinter.\n\n- Susan\n|\nWhat we dream repeatedly, we become.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nNo one but another painter could know the delicacy required to balance the complexities, to keep reality at bay in order to remain in the innermost center of his work.\n\n- Susan Vreeland, Girl in Hyacinth Blue\n|\nMay your adventures bring you closer together, even as they take you far away from home.\n\n- Trenton Lee Stewart, The Mysterious Benedict Society and the Perilous Journey\n|\nLife is a balance between giving and receiving. The more you give, the more abundance will fill your life with joy.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWhen I am king they shall not have bread and shelter only, but also teachings out of books, for a full belly is little worth where the mind is starved.\n\n- Mark Twain, The Prince and the Pauper\n|\n(His WIFE, understanding everything, wants him to stay. MARVIN wants to go. Or MARVIN wants to stay. She wants him to go. Anyway, he's going.)\n\n- William Finn, The Marvin Songs : Three One-Act Musicals\n|\nThis above all: to thine own self be true, And it must follow, as the night the day, Thou canst not then be false to any man.\n\n- William Shakespeare, Hamlet\n|\nWhen we repent by grace, we shall receive times of refreshing from God.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nWe always want to hold on tight to those we love; but if we intend to keep those we love, we must let go every once in awhile.\n\n- Imania\n|\nYou can never recover from losing a person you love, but you can find a way to let it be part of your life rather than letting it take over every part of you\n\n- Darien Gee, Friendship Bread\n|\nCare about people first, then numbers.\n\n- Alin\n|\nTo nourish your soul, see the beauty of nature and feel the love.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nYou're going to make it;You're going to be at peace;You're going to create, and love, and laugh, and live;You're going to do great things.\n\n- Germany\n|\nGratitude enables you to be fearless, and to never shy away from reveling in every moment of your life.\n\n- Janice\n|\nWhatever happens in your life, make a promise to yourself that you will never give up your ability to dream.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nFor every death is a simplification of existence for the others, removes the necessity to show gratitude, the obligation to pay visits.\n\n- Marcel Proust, Time Regained\n|\nIntegrity is doing the right thing when nobody's watching, doing as you say you would do.\n\n- Roy\n|\nHappiness in marriage is a choice you have to make: fight for, protect, pursue. It doesn't happen to you, you make it happen.\n\n- Ngina Otiende, Blues to Bliss: Creating Your Happily-Ever-After In The Early Years\n|\nIf I have nothing but a room full of books, it is enough for me to survive life.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nIf you have life, strength and time, it is enough to perform your sacred task.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nWhat comes from the soul, you can’t fake or learn. You be it, by letting it.\n\n- Dr. Jacinta Mpalyenkana, Ph.D, MBA\n|\nTo go somewhere, start going.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nBut if we are talking in terms of making progress in life, we must understand that 'good enough' is very different from 'best.\n\n- Paulo Coelho, Eleven Minutes\n|\nI believe all Southern liberals come from the same starting point--race. Once you figure out they are lying to you about race, you start to question everything.\n\n- Molly\n|\nI have always wanted to give you the world, so I started giving you pieces of the oceans that kept us apart.\n\n- Karen Quan, Write like no one is reading\n|\nThere is something beautiful about all scars of whatever nature. A scar means the hurt is over, the wound is closed and healed, done with.\n\n- Harry\n|\nGlow wherever you go and let the light of God reflect in the world around you. You carry the light of God and wherever you pass, darkness must flee.\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Become a Better You\n|\nFear of death, wonder at the causes of chance events or unintelligible happenings, hope for divine aid and gratitude for good fortune, cooperated to generate religious belief.\n\n- Will Durant, Our Oriental Heritage\n|\nMen have no more time to understand anything. They buy ready-made things in the shops. But since there are 